article.headline: Northern Kentucky's 3s overwhelm Kennesaw State 78-53
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. -- Tyler White and Todd Johnson combined for nine 3-pointers to lead Northern Kentucky to a 78-53 win over Kennesaw State on Thursday. White led the Norse (12-16, 6-7 Atlantic Sun) with 19 points while making five of seven 3-pointers. Johnson had 12 points on four 3s. Overall, Northern Kentucky made 11 of 21 3-pointers. Yonel Brown led Kennesaw State (10-20, 4-9) with 18 points. Senior Delbert Love had 12 points in his final home game for the Owls. The game, originally scheduled to be played on Wednesday night, was rescheduled due to a winter storm in North Georgia. Northern Kentucky moved into a tie with Lipscomb for fourth in the Atlantic Sun. The Norse close their regular season against USC Upstate on Saturday. Kennesaw State will play Lipscomb.
